table-0096-756.caption: Development
data: Centre door omitted and wide wrap-round doors at the ends. Space saved by removal of the centre vestibule used to move toilets to one at each end instead of two at one end, as previously. Red folding plastic gangway doors and vestibule ends.
As Mk2b, with lowered ceiling with provision for ducts for air conditioning (never fitted). Red folding plastic gangway doors and vestibule ends.

Air conditioned so no opening windows in the seating area, glass area reduced, windows tinted. Electric heating only from here onward. Mk2d FKs and BFKs were the last locomotive-hauled side-corridor compartment coaches constructed for British Railways, other than sleeping cars. Red folding plastic gangway doors and vestibule ends.
Luggage racks fitted opposite toilet cubicles, which were reduced in size. Cream folding plastic gangway doors and vestibule ends.

Interior panelling made of plastic, new-style seating, automatic gangway doors, lower bodyside heaters. These features had first debuted on the Mark 3 prototypes. Cream folding plastic gangway doors and vestibule ends.

table-0096-155.caption: May 31 New York event
data: This tornado had a total path length of miles (km), crossing through 3 counties and 2 states (NY and VT). 350 homes and businesses damaged or destroyed along its entire track, 68 injuries, and about $70M in damage. There was also extensive forest damage. Width was 970yards. In Vermont, extensive F2 damage occurred to homes. Damage was $630,000. Width was 200yards.
This was a small tornado that crossed the Albany International Airport and the New York State Thruway. It was 75yards wide and produced $25,000 in damage.
Small tornado which produced $150,000 in damage. Width was 75yards.
Small tornado which caused 2 injuries and $90,000 in damage. Width was 25yards.

In Tioga County, it was a small tornado which skipped along hilltops causing $50,000 in damage. Width was 50yards. In Broome County, it was a large tornado which moved through the Town of Binghamton. This tornado made a direct hit on the local ABC affiliate television station causing major damage. This is a continuation of the above Tioga County tornado. This moved through 3 counties and had a discontinuous total path length of over 60miles. 12people were injured and it produced $1.5M in damages. Width was 200yards. In Delaware County, this tornado caused severe damage to several homes and forested areas. Baseball sized hail was reported falling from this thunderstorm. Damage approached $1million. Width was 200yards.
This tornado was short lived but had a massive width of over 1500yards. It produced $500,000 in damage.
This tornado caused heavy damage to forested areas and several homes. 3people were injured, and $800,000 worth of damage occurred. The path was 800yards wide.
A shed was destroyed and the roof of a lumberyard building was blown off

title: [Snakehead_(fish)|Snakehead]
This is a fish commonly found in the calm waters of a wetland with almost no wave movement. The Snakehead is also referred to as the “tyrant of freshwater.”
table-0096-924.caption: Fish and Shell Fish
data: Found throughout the wetland due to its highly adaptive nature, the Crucian Carp maintains an omnivorous diet of insects, shell fish, seeds, leafs, stalks of plants and other organic material.
Catfish live in relatively shallow waters around the wetland that has low fluid speed and mud on the bottom. The Catfish is nocturnal and feeds primarily on fry and small animals.

A flat fish with a small mouth, the Rhodeus ocellatus can be found throughout the wetlands. During the breeding season the male’s eyes, chest, abdomen and fins change different colors to attract mates.

As flat as a willow leaf and as common as the Crucian Carp, the Fighting Fish is frequently found in the upper stream of Topyeongcheon (stream) surrounded by a lot of water planets and slow moving water.

Rice Paddy Freshwater Snails can be found crawling on the muddy floor or living in the leaves or stalks of water chestnuts. The snails primarily feed on germs and bacteria in the mud, keeping the water of the wetland from getting rot.
Living on the floor of the wetland like the Rice Paddy Freshwater Snail, the Daechingi is a kind of clam that has suffered a decline in its population due to increased amounts of pollution.
The Mussel has a thick, large, black shell, easily distinguishable from similar species by a growth vein and a distinctively dark brown ligament.
Slightly longer than the Rice Paddy Freshwater Snail, the Freshwater Snail filters out mud by moving as though it were painting a picture.
